Onto some good news from the banking sector. The African guarantee fund AGF&nbsp;and equity group holdings plc have signed an agreement,&nbsp;which will provide an 8.25 billion shillings&nbsp;guarantee fund to four of equity&rsquo;s bank subsidiaries within the group. *** the facility is earmarked to support equity to scale up its lending activities to women owned and managed micro, small and medium sized enterprises in Kenya, Uganda, Rwanda and the DRC, ensuring women are able to access cheap credit.&nbsp;Speaking during the signing ceremony, Equitys CEO Dr. James Mwangi, stated that, the facility from African guarantee fund, will strongly position the bank at a time when appetite for credit gathers momentum in the economy. &nbsp;